Ad Text:
BOORTMALT is a multinational organisation owned by the French cooperative AXEREAL. Our global organisation is focused on producing an extensive range of high-quality malt types to meet the exacting requirements of our brewing and distilling customers around the world. Our mission is to be the best innovative malt supplier, producing quality malts in benchmark maltings.

Based in our Head Office in Melbourne and reporting to the Chief Financial Officer, this is a wonderful opportunity for a suitably experienced finance professional to join our close-knit team.

The Commercial and Reporting Analyst (Decision Support) delivers financial analysis that provides insight to support business decision making. The role provides a view on business performance and assists in highlighting opportunities for business improvement and optimization. Additionally, this role provides timely and accurate reporting and analysis of APAC gross margins and profitability and effectively manages the finance reporting environment. A key member of the finance team, this role leads financial management reporting and annual finance planning processes. Tasks will include:

Reporting and analysing financial data to report on APAC Group Financial performance in a monthly and timely manner;

Analysing financial data to identify trends, risks, and opportunities, including those related to changing regulation and standards;

Preparing and presenting financial reports to senior management;

Optimising, standardising or developing reports where opportunity exists;

Ensuring Master data accuracy across the Gross Margin area, particularly as it relates to Cost Card (Expected Costs);

Contributing to Group financial process improvement and maintain controls integrity;

Managing and overseeing annual budgeting, long-range financial planning, and forecasting processes

Developing and maintaining complex financial models, including scenario analysis, to support decision-making;

Collaborating  with departments like sales, marketing, and operations to ensure financial plans align with strategic goals;

Driving improvements in financial processes, systems, and reporting capabilities to increase efficiency and accuracy;

Maintaining group financial reporting systems ensuring timely and accurate reporting of regional results.

As Masters of Malt, we want to be a great employer, focusing on flexibility, inclusion, collaboration and health and wellbeing. We live our values, putting people at the heart of what we do. If you have the appropriate level of finance specific skills, qualifications and experience, including ERP, systems and reporting aptitude, then we would love to hear from you.
